LAGOS  – Asso Leadership Academy, Lagos, an academy designed to mentor entrepreneurs and business leaders to scale their businesses geometrically has turned five. According to Austin Okere, the founder of the academy, Asso Leadership Academy is for mentoring business executives and entrepreneurs, adding that the idea is that businesses and entrepreneurs have a need for their people to be able to take the business forward in succession. He said Asso Leadership Academy is mentoring business executives and entrepreneurs, adding that the idea is that businesses and entrepreneurs have a need for their people to be able to take the business forward in succession. According to him, for those who have growth plans and want to attract capital, “we will introduce them to investors and would be investors. These are the things we are doing for entrepreneurs.”